title: High School Football Sectional pairings set
text:
High School Football Sectional pairings set 
By WISE Web Sports High School Football Sectional pairings set October 11, 2015 Updated Oct 11, 2015 at 7:37 PM EDT 
(Indianapolis, Indiana) -- The draw was made for the 2015 High School Football Sectionals Sunday night in Indianapolis. The pairings for the teams in Northeast Indiana are: (6A) Warsaw at Carroll and Northrop. (5A) Concord at North Side, Goshen at Snider, and Huntington North at Anderson. (4A) East Noble at Northwood, Columbia City at Northridge, Wawasee at Plymouth, DeKalb at Angola, Marion at South Side, Logansport at Leo, Bishop Dwenger at Wayne, and New Haven at Mississinewa, (3A) Lakeland at Heritage, Fairfield at Culver Academies, Garrett at West Noble, Tippecanoe Valley at Jimtown, Bellmont at Maconaquah, Norwell at Concordia, and Bishop Luers at Northwestern. (2A) South Adams at Churubusco, Prairie Heights at Whitko, Bluffton at Eastside, and Woodlan at Central Noble. (1A) Southern Wells at Union City and Adams Central at Wes - Del. Some sectionals begin October 23 rd while others start October 30 th.   To submit a comment on this article, your email address is required.
